.TH SHELL " 16 August 2024" "Simple Shell" "man page"

.SH NAME
.B holberton simple shell
\- Minimalistic Unix command line interpreter


.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [command] " " [argument]

.SH DESCRIPTION

Holberton simple shell, is a custom implementation of a simple  Unix command line interpreter that executes commands from a user terminal. The
shell. A minimalistic approach was taken in its desing and implementation to only provide the basic
functions of a shell similar to the deseing by the pioneer of Unix shells, Ken Thompson. Desing,
          compilation. Reads commands from standard intput and executes them.

          .SH OVERVIEW

          Similar to other legendary command line interfaces, the simple_shell takes input from either the
          terminal or scripts and executes them as they appear.

          Then, run the following command to open the simple shell:

          .nf
          .B ./hsh
          .fi

          .SH LIBRARIES USED
          The following libraries and definitions are used in this project:

          .nf
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <sys/types.h>
#include <sys/wait.h>
          .fi

          .SH USE
          The simple shell is a Unix command line interpreter.
          It will interpreters the first word as a command, and the following as the series of arguments.

          Examples:
          .nf
          .B ./hsh
          $ ls -l
          $ pwd
          $ exit
          .fi

          .SH SEE ALSO
          .BR shell
          .BR bash

